mkdir testdir

touch testfile.txt

cat > testfile.txt (fdgrthrthtrh)

cp testfile.txt copyfile.txt

RENAME A FILE : moving a file and renaming a file is the same process.

mv testfile.txt origfile.txt

move a file without renaming? specify a location and no file name :

mkdir subdir1

mv origfile.txt subdir1

move and rename at the same time? :

mv origfile.txt ../testfile.txt

DELETE FILES :

rm copyfile.txt   (be careful with rm)

remove directories? :

cp -r testdir copydir (copies contents)

mkdir dir2

cp -r testdir dir2 (copies entire directory and contents because exists)

RENAME : mv testdir origdir

MOVE DIRECTORY: mv origdir copydir

cd copydir

move and rename ? :

mv origdir ../testdir

delete directory? :

cd ..

rm -r copydir

rm -rf testdir (forced, recursive {directory})

